## Git Workflow

This is the `work`-repo crew workflow.

- Do not directly push or merge to the target branch by default.
- Treat branch/PR-oriented handling as the safe default for this rig class.
- For smaller, scoped tasks, prefer the work-pack worker flow and its branch-ready
  handoff behavior.
- For larger work you keep in crew, follow the same trust boundary: verify the
  work, push the branch/work as the workflow expects, and hand off cleanly for
  review or downstream follow-up.
- Repo-specific docs may add required checks or commands, but they should not
  weaken the `work` trust boundary.

